    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The end times are here - the Great Lord of Fire has decreed it! Let everything burn!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Fernageddon is a RPG/strategy game, with the focus on character development, finding loot, and tactical turn-based combat. <br>Oh, and burning things. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Begin as a humble aspiring champion to the Great Fire God. Slowly gain skills and favour, learn spells, find followers and legendary weapons.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Eventually, if you succeed, demonhood beckons...  And having gone so far, it seems only fair to try and assume the great fiery throne, too... </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>FEATURES</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >A deep and detailed turn-based combat system with many factors determining success. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Explore the world in 3D - find lost dungeons, mighty cities and legendary locations.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Fight numerous enemies, from the mundane (militia and raiders), to the exotic (elves and dwarfs), to the monstrous (dragons and demons).</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Gain experience with each fight and develop your skills. (about 200!) </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >52 different professions! (Initial choice of 4 which branch into others at level 5 and 10)</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Gain glory with each conquest, and gain gifts from the Fire God.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Recruit a great army of followers - man, beast and even horrors from beyond...</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Fail to please your fickle master and His ennui will rise - if this gets too high, He will give you &quot;rewards&quot; of His own choosing...</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Burn them all and bring on The Fernageddon!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >** New - Heretic mode - fight an open-ended battle against the evil minions of fire instead! </p>",
